mads:mads.mads:note:
Dict. of Greek and Roman biog. and mythology, 1967: v. 1, p. 351-352;
      &#034;Cornelia&#034;, #5 (Cornelia; younger daughter of Scipio Africanus the
      elder; married to Ti. Sempronius Gracchus; mother of the two tribunes Tiberius and Gaius;
      mother-in-law of Scipio Africanus the Younger; retired to Misenum after the death of her sons,
      where she remained in contact with prominent figures; upon her death, the Roman people erected
      a statue to her with the inscription Cornelia, mother of the Gracchi)
